reviews.title: First acquaintance: nice terrace and smooth service!
reviews.text: As a former Customer of café Koekenbier I had washed up here a long time ago and back then it was still a business with ladies with strollers and coffee with apple pie and whipped cream. With AMI, there is now a real café on this spot. We came here for drinks with a bitter garnish. Friendly welcome by the staff and smooth service. Fine bitter garnish and the Pinot Grigio we ordered was of reasonable quality. As usual we enjoyed this beautiful, sunny terrace again. We will definitely be back here, but for a better wine.
